Instead of Parliament enacting legislative measures to cushion ordinary citizens, MPs were busy in political rallies.
Before I chide the politicians, the people are equally to blame. We watched citizens troop to political rallies in defiance of the Ministry of Health’s Covid-19 guidelines. They listened and cheered as the politicians addressed their ambitions, instead of pressing concerns such as the effects of pandemic.
The Constitution bestows sovereignty on the people. This sovereignty should not just be exercised every five years when we elect our leaders but every other time in holding them accountable. It is ridiculous when elected officials yell on social media and in rallies instead of using their positions to push for changes.



