The media has been busy interviewing government officials about their experience with Covid-19. What the officials do not say is that had they been left in the care of local public hospitals, they could now be in the other world, perhaps singing with the angels or answering for their sins. Health workers are on strike. Little is said of that.
More political seats
The ordinary parent’s most pressing concern is not whether or not the son of a peasant can be President or the addition of more political seats, but whether they can take their child to school and access health care.



